23#include "mpfr-impl.h"
24
25int
26mpfr_mul_2si (mpfr_ptr y, mpfr_srcptr x, long int n, mpfr_rnd_t rnd_mode)
27{
28 int inexact;
29
30 MPFR_LOG_FUNC
31 (("x[%Pu]=%.*Rg n=%ld rnd=%d",
32 mpfr_get_prec (x), mpfr_log_prec, x, n, rnd_mode),
33 ("y[%Pu]=%.*Rg inexact=%d",
34 mpfr_get_prec (y), mpfr_log_prec, y, inexact));
35
36 if (MPFR_UNLIKELY (MPFR_IS_SINGULAR (x)))
37 return mpfr_set (y, x, rnd_mode);
38 else
39 {
40 mpfr_exp_t exp = MPFR_GET_EXP (x);
41 MPFR_SETRAW (inexact, y, x, exp, rnd_mode);
42 if (MPFR_UNLIKELY(n >= 0 && (__gmpfr_emax < MPFR_EMIN_MIN + n ||
43 exp > __gmpfr_emax - n)))
44 return mpfr_overflow (y, rnd_mode, MPFR_SIGN(y));
45 else if (MPFR_UNLIKELY(n < 0 && (__gmpfr_emin > MPFR_EMAX_MAX + n ||
46 exp < __gmpfr_emin - n)))
47 {
48 if (rnd_mode == MPFR_RNDN &&
49 (__gmpfr_emin > MPFR_EMAX_MAX + (n + 1) ||
50 exp < __gmpfr_emin - (n + 1) ||
51 ((MPFR_IS_NEG (y) ? inexact <= 0 : inexact >= 0) &&
52 mpfr_powerof2_raw (y))))
53 rnd_mode = MPFR_RNDZ;
54 return mpfr_underflow (y, rnd_mode, MPFR_SIGN(y));
55 }
56 MPFR_SET_EXP (y, exp + n);
57 }
58
59 MPFR_RET (inexact);
60}
